The input \( v_i = \cos(\omega_0 t) \) can be expressed in phasor form as \( \text{Re}\{e^{j\omega_0 t}\} \). Applying the transfer function \( H(\omega_0) = |H(\omega_0)| e^{-j\phi} \) yields the output phasor \( |H(\omega_0)| e^{-j\phi} e^{j\omega_0 t} \), whose inverse Fourier transform gives \( |H(\omega_0)| \cos(\omega_0 t - \phi) \).

\boxed{D}
